\f1\b0\fs38 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\ql\qnatural

\b \cf2 Serves: 
\b0 \cf0 8 portions\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 cup almonds, preferably marcona\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup loosely packed fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/basil/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 basil}} leaves\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon freshly cracked black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1/4 cups shredded {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/asiago/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Asiago}} cheese, divided\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/3 cup olive oil\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 loaf sweet {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/french-bread/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 French bread}} or {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/sourdough/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 sourdough}}\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.\
In a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/food-processor/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 food processor}}, add the almonds and pulse until they are finely chopped. Add the basil, black pepper and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cinnamon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cinnamon}} and process until incorporated. Add 1 cup of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cheese/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cheese}}, pulse a few times, then with the machine still running, slowly add in the olive oil.\
Cut the bread in half, spread it with the pesto and bake on a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cookie/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cookie}} sheet for 7 to 10 minutes. At this point, remove the bread, sprinkle it with the remaining 1/3 cup of cheese and turn on the broiler. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/broil/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Broil}} the bread until the cheese has melted and starting to brown. Remove from the oven, cut it into 8 portions and serve immediately.\
